The paper discusses the development of a middleware to address the problem of communication and synchronization of distributed models, specifically in the context of medical best-practice models. This involves the use of statechart-based model-driven development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the need for efficient communication architecture and queuing mechanisms, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The focus on ensuring compliance with the semantics of statechart-based development suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. Finally, the paper highlights the potential benefits for clinicians and medical staff, indicating a potential application in healthcare (cs.HC).
